OL,3,CFootball fan 'ashamed' and hopes
OL,4,Cothers 'think twice' about tragedy
OL,5,Cchanting
OL,7,FA Manchester United supporter says he
OL,8,Fis "ashamed" and hopes other fans
OL,9,F"think twice" after being convicted of
OL,10,F"tragedy chanting".
OL,12,FMichael Avery, 45, pleaded guilty to a
OL,13,Fpublic order offence after making
OL,14,Fgestures related to the Hillsborough
OL,15,Fand Heysel stadium disasters at the FA
OL,16,FCup quarter-final between and .
OL,18,FAvery who was given a three-year
OL,19,Ffootball banning order and ordered to
OL,20,Fpay #1,205, said he was "deeply sorry".
